				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-8836329/scp-4549#post-4132542</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 27 Jan 2019 15:00:53 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>WarpZone</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>147364</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Is everybody employed by the entire Foundation just <em>terrible</em> at negotiations? Seems like half the interviews I've ever read on this site consist of Cover Story, followed by Overt Question That Lays All The Foundation's Cards On The Table, followed by The Poi Pointing Out That The Cards Played Consist of A Monopoly Property, A Shiny Charmander, And An Expired Library Card, then the Poi Immediately Ends The Meeting Revealing Nothing. The audience doesn't gain any new information, and I just feel dumb for having expected anything interesting to happen.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
